To trigger a backup NOW (for testing):
Run this in AWS CloudShell or ask your runner to execute it:

aws backup start-backup-job \
  --backup-vault-name sap-hana-backup-vault \
  --resource-arn arn:aws:ec2:us-east-1:677277859823:instance/i-0d939938273696777 \
  --iam-role-arn arn:aws:iam::677277859823:role/sap-hana-backup-role
Replace i-0d939938273696777 with your actual instance ID from instance_list.txt.

To check if the backup plan is active:
aws backup list-backup-plans --query 'BackupPlansList[].[BackupPlanName,BackupPlanId]' --output table
To check upcoming scheduled jobs:
Go to AWS Console → AWS Backup → Jobs → Backup jobs — you'll see scheduled jobs listed there once the next window starts.

